column1: #: description: Tagging efficiency for AK8 jets. The efficiency includes the effect of the machine-learning based DeepAK8 tagger
column2: as well as the application of the mass window requirement on the jet. The efficiency is split depending on the matching generator-level object. For reinterpretation purposes
column3: this efficiency can directly be applied to any AK8 jet that is matched to a given type of generator-level object
column4: with no prior selection on the jet mass. Other acceptance requirements on jet $\p_{T}$ and $\eta$ should still be applied.

column1: #: keyword reactions: P P --> Z0 | P P --> W+ | P P --> W- | P P --> JET JET
#: keyword phrases: DeepAK8 | Jet tagging | mono-V
